                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-245-off1296 t18281204-245-crimeloc1299"></join> - he had a sale there. I saw the prisoner while the sale was going on - I was watching him for nearly an hour; I did not see him take any thing, but I met him as I was going up stairs - I received information, and followed him; I called to him - he stopped when he had got about forty yards; I went up, and told him I had a suspision he had something on his person - he made some answer, but I cannot exactly tell what; I said "Come, take off your hat, and let me have it - he took off his hat, and gave me one of the cups; I brought him back before Mr. Foster; he said it was a mistake; I was taking him to the watch-house, and he gave me the other cup and saucers out of his pocket.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 25.</p>
